================================================================================
Third-Party Dependencies and Licenses
================================================================================

This software uses the following third-party dependencies:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HashiCorp Vault API
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
License: Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
Source: https://github.com/hashicorp/vault

The MPL-2.0 is a weak copyleft license. It requires that modifications to
MPL-licensed files be released under the MPL, but allows combining with
proprietary code. Sovra uses the Vault API client library without modification.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OpenTelemetry Go Instrumentation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
License: LGPL-2.1 (transitive dependency)
Source: https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go-instrumentation

The LGPL-2.1 allows linking with proprietary software without requiring the
proprietary software to be released under the LGPL, provided the LGPL-licensed
component is not modified. This is a transitive dependency through the
OpenTelemetry ecosystem.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Other Dependencies
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Most dependencies are licensed under permissive licenses (Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD):

- github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 - MIT License
- github.com/google/uuid - BSD-3-Clause
- github.com/lib/pq - MIT License
- github.com/open-policy-agent/opa - Apache-2.0
- github.com/testcontainers/testcontainers-go - MIT License
- And others (see go.mod for full list)

For the complete list of dependencies and their licenses, see:
https://app.fossa.com/projects/git%2Bgithub.com%2Fwitlox%2Fsovra

================================================================================
License Compatibility
================================================================================

Sovra is licensed under the Apache License 2.0. The use of MPL-2.0 and LGPL-2.1
licensed dependencies is compatible with Apache-2.0:

- MPL-2.0: File-level copyleft only; compatible with Apache-2.0
- LGPL-2.1: Allows linking; compatible when used as a library

No modifications have been made to any copyleft-licensed code.
